The first time I saw Matthew Macfadyen was in a PBS miniseries years ago, called "Any Human Heart."  I thought, Wow, who's this? He's a great actor, but for me, Colin Firth will always be Mr. Darcy.  

If you belong to PBS you may be able to find "Any Human Heart" in their archives.  It had everything from sly and funny to utterly heartbreaking. The story is about a writer, starting out in the 1920's and following him into the 1950s.

